LessonLearned

Target IP: 10.10.53.2

Challenge Description: Have you learned your lesson?

Reconnaissance



There are only two TCP ports open on the target machine: SSH and HTTP, as shown above. I will start enumeration with the HTTP application on port 80.

Exploitation & Flag

Port 80: HTTP

Browsing to this port displays the webpage above. Spraying default credentials did not work.


Testing for SQL injection in the username field using the payload admin' OR '1'='1' -- // displays the webpage above. This challenge does not like the use of OR '1'='1'; therefore, it hints me to use a less destructive payload to bypass the login. I will need to reset the box and try again.


Before injecting a safer payload, I will need to find the possible usernames. I achieved this by using the command hydra -L /usr/share/wordlists/seclists/Usernames/xato-net-10-million-usernames.txt -p test 10.10.162.0 http-post-form "/index.php:username=^USER^&password=^PASS^:Invalid username and password.". In the image above, I obtained the possible valid usernames. I will use one of the valid username, like martin, to bypass the login.


And using a safer payload like martin' -- - works. The flag is shown above. The lesson here is to not use OR 1=1 payload as it may get processed by UPDATE or DELETE statement, causing the modification or deletion of each row in the table. It is safer to use AND 1=1 with a valid input such as a username.
